            <h3>State Waste Management Framework</h3>
            <p>Illinois operates under the Environmental Protection Act (415 ILCS 5), which establishes comprehensive waste management requirements overseen by the Illinois Environmental Protection Agency (EPA). The state mandates a 50% waste diversion goal and has specific regulations for bulky waste items including mattresses through the Illinois Solid Waste Management Act.</p>
            
            <h3>Municipal Bulk Waste Requirements</h3>
            <p>Illinois municipalities, particularly in Cook County and Chicago metro area, have ordinances requiring special scheduling for mattress collection. Chicago's Department of Streets and Sanitation requires advance scheduling for bulk items, with mattresses classified as "large items" requiring separate collection protocols from regular residential waste.</p>
            
            <h3>Landfill Disposal Fees & Regulations</h3>
            <p>Illinois operates under a landfill tax system with fees ranging from $2.00 to $4.95 per ton depending on facility type and location. Cook County maintains additional tipping fees, making professional recycling services cost-effective for mattress disposal while supporting the state's waste diversion objectives.</p>
            
            <h3>Recycling Facility Standards</h3>
            <p>Materials Recovery Facilities processing mattresses must obtain permits from Illinois EPA under 35 Ill. Adm. Code 807. Facilities must demonstrate compliance with air quality standards, storm water management, and proper materials separation to maintain operational permits throughout Illinois.</p>
        </div>
        
